wikipedia_page.main: James Herbert Alexander Lyske (7 October 1932 – 1974) was a Northern Irish footballer who played as a full back in the Irish Football League for Glenavon, in the English Football League for Darlington, and for Southern League club Yeovil Town. He was on the books of Sunderland without playing for them in the League.Lyske played four times for Ireland Schools in 1947 and represented Northern Ireland youth in 1951.
